{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT's text production algorithm was developed and honed in a process quite similar to artificial selection.",
    "Functions and selection processes have the same sort of directedness that human intentions do; naturalistic philosophers of mind have long connected them to the intentionality of human and animal mental states.",
    "If ChatGPT is understood as having intentions or intention-like states in this way, its intention is to present itself in a certain way (as a conversational agent or interlocutor) rather than to represent and convey facts.",
    "In other words, it has the intentions we associate with hard bullshitting.",
    "One way we can think of ChatGPT as having intentions is by adopting Dennett's intentional stance towards it."
  ]
}